parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power, engine damage, and potentially a fire, which can result in an accident or injury.
symptoms: Burning hot anti-freeze
steam clouding the cabin
engine overheating
loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the timing belt can cause engine damage, stalling, and potentially lead to an accident or injury.
symptoms: Timing belt failure
engine stalling
damage to valves
engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the instrument panel can cause inaccurate readings, leading to a loss of vehicle control, and potentially an accident or injury.
symptoms: Temperature and gas gauges fixed on many occasions but never fully fixed
work only when pushed on the dash cover.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power windows can cause inconvenience, water damage, and safety risks due to stuck windows.
symptoms: Power windows suddenly stop working
windows stuck in the up or down position
inability to roll windows up or down
water damage due to stuck windows.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause smoke to fill the car, potentially leading to accidents or health risks.
symptoms: Smoke fills the car while driving
heater core breaks
smoke comes out of the ventilation switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater fan motor can cause the unit to melt and burn, potentially leading to accidents or fires.
symptoms: Heater fan fails
unit melts and burns
fan switch burns out
selector face melts.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Injector System Failure - Accumulator/Delivery System Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks from the accumulator/delivery system can cause strong gas fumes, potentially leading to a fire hazard, especially when stopping or when the air conditioning system is turned on.
symptoms: Strong gas fumes inside and outside the vehicle
fuel pouring out of the system
gas leaks onto the air conditioner clutch
fuel leaks near the rear right wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the differential pressure regulator can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to a fire hazard, especially when the air conditioning system is turned on.
symptoms: Gas fumes inside the vehicle
fuel leaks onto the air conditioner clutch
delamination of the plastic body from the brass core
structural failure of the regulator mounted on the fuel distributor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking of the fuel pump container can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to a fire hazard, especially when someone is near the vehicle with an open flame.
symptoms: Fuel leaks near the rear right wheel
fuel leaks from the cracked container
vibration suspected as the cause of the crack.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The tampering of the odometer reading can lead to a lack of transparency in the vehicle's history, potentially causing buyers to overpay for a vehicle or be unaware of underlying issues.
symptoms: Odometer reading is inconsistent or appears to be rolled back
discrepancy in the vehicle's maintenance records
mismatch between the odometer reading and the vehicle's condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of an ignition interlock system can allow the vehicle to be shifted into gear without the key in the ignition, potentially leading to accidents or unintended vehicle movement.
symptoms: Vehicle can be shifted into gear without the key in the ignition
lack of warning or notification when attempting to shift into gear without the key.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seatbelt system can cause the seatbelts to malfunction, leading to a potential safety risk in the event of an accident. The system's failure to properly restrain occupants can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seatbelts fail to operate properly
the seatbelts open while driving
the seatbelts stay open
the seatbelt retractors do not work
the seatbelt system drains the car's battery.
